track_notes: Hiked in 2022 August. Recent forest fire burned down most of the lower east side of the creek. There are many trees across the trail. You may lose the trail as well. Once you cross the creek the 2nd time trail can be a bit overgrown before the talus field. Upper section was not affected by the fires. Once reached the saddle turn west and up. Follow sign Mt. Baldy here. Good footpath leads up to the upper meadows. Gaining access to the ridgeline is not difficult. Try stay high on ridgeline. I was trying to avoid ups and downs by staying lower and ended up up in bad bushwhack. Decent size flat summit area, no register. Class 2 scramble.
